block and inline element
A block-level element always starts on a new line.A block-level element always takes up the full width available.

An inline element does not start on a new line.An inline element only takes up as much width as necessary.


To make a cell span over multiple columns, use the colspan attribute:
that is <h1 colspan="2">name<h1/>      so it will convert (col) cell  2 into 1.
that is <h1 rowspan="2">name<h1/>      so it will convert (row)  cell 2 into 2.


The Target Attribute:
_blank	Opens the linked document in a new window or tab
_self	Opens the linked document in the same frame as it was clicked (this is default)
_parent	Opens the linked document in the parent frame
_top	Opens the linked document in the full body of the window
framename	Opens the linked document in the named iframe




CSS Selectors
Simple selectors (select elements based on name, id, class,group)
Combinator selectors (select elements based on a specific relationship between them)
Pseudo-class selectors (select elements based on a certain state)
Pseudo-elements selectors (select and style a part of an element)
Attribute selectors (select elements based on an attribute or attribute value)

Combinator selectors
descendant selector (space):slelect all p of div
child selector (>):select only child p of div
adjacent sibling selector (+)adjacant p outside div
general sibling selector (~):select all p outside div.

Pseudo-class selectors
A pseudo-class is used to define a special state of an element.
like to an anchor tag this is used to style like 
a:hover a:visited


Pseudo-elements selectors
Style the first letter, or line, of an element
Insert content before, or after, the content of an element
p::first-letter


Opacity:
default opacity is 1.
The opacity property can take a value from 0.0 - 1.0.